    <h2> Enjoyment </h2>
    <p> Kpop is a remedy to many. It has helped many people. We all are going through personal problems and music is a healing.  </p> 
 
<p> Kpop as a whole has really helped me. Personally, I have changed and developed better through all the things I have learned through kpop. I have met such amazing people all across the internet through a band. I have gotten through some of my toughest times due to music. It helped me think of thoughts I long had forgotten existed.  </p>
 
 
 
<p> The relationships that are built through kpop are the ones that seem like they would last your entire life. SO many pure and precious moments and memories. From the time you commit to the time you decide it's time to quit. All the love that is spread is very wholesome. Although so much of westerm media shows the "bad" side of kpop, it's not that deep.</p>
 
<p> Once you enter there is no exit. You might find one but it's a long way in a dark hallway, struggling to find the lightswitch. The emotional and financial commitment that is made during the time is very deep. Through kpop i was able to develop and know my true self. All the ugly and pretty is all there, but it’s all a part of me.</p>
 
<p> <b> One strong message I've learned is “It’s okay to not be okay”. <b>  </p>
 
<p> That everything will be okay eventually. You must remember that pain is temporary. It takes time to let your wounds heal. It'll leave a scar but the wounds will close.</p>
