  <div class="column middle">
     <h2> Kpop </h2>
    <p> Kpop is Korean Pop music that originated from South Korea.
     Kpop is not limited to pop music but the most popular genre is pop so it is referred to Kpop. 
   It has largely dominated the music industry in past few years due to this idol group named BTS. Another popular male idol group that has been around since a very long time is SHINEE. SHINEE, a once 5 member group, debuted in the year of 2008. 
</p>
 
    <p> Kpop has faced a lot of criticism since it hit the western regions. One common question that is asked to korean groups is “why do you think kpop is so popular?”. One of my personal favorite answers is “It’s just music in another language. The same way we listen to ‘American’ music is the same way others listen to our songs”. </p>
    
    
   
    <p> Music is music no matter the language. There is no limit to it. We listen to latin/spanish, english, french. There should be no barrier and gates to the music industry in the sense of language. We all are born and raised differently yet there are thousands and thousands of people who are listening to the same song.  </p>
    
     <p> Another kpop embraces and spreads is the bond. The bond between the fan and group is so beautiful and special. Millions of people of different ages, religions, gender are coming together to listen to kpop. It is amazing to see the unity in concert video and images. </p> 
    
  </div>
  
  <div class="column side">
    <h2> Platforms </h2>
    <p> There are many platforms for kpop groups and soloists. One common platform is Twitter. There is something related to kpop trending every other day. Another large platform is Vlive/Vlive+. Vlive is a broadcasting app/site where idols would go live (as in instagram live). One platform for debuts and comebacks is Mnet. Mnet is famously known for debut and comeback stages. Once in a while there would be special stages.  </p>
       
         <p> Other platforms are stages such as MAMA, GDA,  SBS Music Awards and many more. They would be award shows at the end of the year or during comeback season. They are similar to the VMA’s and Grammy’s. </p>
   
    <p> Other events idol groups would attend are promotional shows to promote their music. During their comeback time they would also do a reality show and have behind the scenes of their music shows and concerts. One common video service would be documentary where it would show the real and raw behind the scenes. All the sacrifices that are made to complete the comeback/concert. </p>
    
    <p> Another place idols openly and actively communicate through is bubble, weverse and fansign events. Bubble is a personal chat between the chosen member and a fan. Weverse is an open platform similar to instagram and the artist may or may not see the post. Fansign events are run during comeback season and it has its own rules and regulations.
    
  </div>
